tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The blood count is largely within normal limits. There is a mildly decreased hematocrit, with hemoglobin at the lower end of normal, suggesting possible borderline anemia. Platelet count is normal, but platelet distribution width is elevated, which may indicate increased platelet size variability, often seen in reactive states. No acute abnormalities detected; clinical correlation is recommended.
